          <p class='first-para'>
            I am grateful to the noble Lord, Lord Goodhart, for his intervention. He has raised more matters on which I need to ask questions between now and Report so that I am clear in my mind. I believe that it would be helpful for the noble and learned Lord the Attorney-General to stand back and look at the application of legal representation in this particular circumstance.</p><p>
            The noble and learned Lord quoted the <span class="italic">Wickes</span> trial and said that it was particularly analogous to this issue. It may relate to the seriousness of the offences committed, but in the <span class="italic">Wickes</span> trial that was not proved. The noble and learned Lord may look rather ruefully in this case.</p><p>
            Certainly the Minister has given me cause to consider the matter between now and Report. It may be more helpful if I contact the Bill team and raise one or two issues with them. Following discussion, we may be able to avoid tabling an amendment on Report I beg leave to withdraw the amendment.
          </p>
        </blockquote>
      </div>
      <a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_46gc' title='Col. 46GC &mdash; HL Deb 13 January 2003 vol 643 c46GC' name='column_46gc' href='#column_46gc' rel='bookmark'>46GC</a>
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0643P0-01081'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0643P0_20030113_GCR_212' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
